	   <tr><td colspan=2>I know this question was addressed to Mightion, but I'm guessing you wanted a more concete answer, so I'm adding my 2cp.<br><br>In my experience (i'm not there yet, Skill 145), I am spending about 200pp per skill point if I try to just power my skill up. I'd imagine that will probably double at 168 when mantles trivial and I have to use cloaks to get to 175. Past that point, I have no clue, although I would guess that 1-2k plat per skill point might be about right. Everything I hear says 190 is the skill level you want before trying the Imbued field plate. Therefore, using my estimates, I would venture that it would cost you about:<br><br>8200pp to get to 168<br>2800pp to get to 175<br>30000pp to get to 190<br>-------<br>41k plat total. Thats assuming the high end of all my estimates. Half that if you get really lucky. BTW the info I presented I got primarily from the smithing forum on eqtraders.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
