	   <tr><td colspan=2>On my server on Xev, (Guild shall remain nameless, of course) as the guildmaster of my guild with a blacksmithing skill of 244, together with my two buddies, we make tonnes of cultural armour. I am a Barbarian Shaman, my buddy is a High Elf, and my other friend is a Human. Between the 3 of us, we make Northman armour, Field Plate and Mithril armor, and the imbued versions, Tribunal, Mith Marr and Tunare respectively. In our guild we have a kind of a thing going on.<br>The 3 of us have been playing for over 2 years now, and granted we never made 60 (spent so much time having fun instead of leveling) we broke off from an Uber Guild on our server, and created our own newbie guild. Every week on the sunday, We each make a few pieces of the types of armor for our newbie members. And we give them a 'Quest' of sorts. <br>Like last week we had this quest, a Tunare worshiping High elf magician in our guild wanted to get the Imbued Mithril BP (wearble by casters), so we gave him this quest.<br>Bring me;<br>1- Shadow Wolf Pelt<br>2- Rune of Karana<br>3- Plains Pebble<br>4- Flowing Black Robe<br>5- Orc Pawn Scalp<br>6- Blackburrow Gnoll Pelt<br>7- Greater Lightstone<br>8- Oak Leaf<br><br>And we gave him 3 hours to gather all the items together. But he wasn't able to,.. but he begged us for another few more hours.... hey we already made the thing in anticipation for giving to him so we said heck we'll wait some more.<br>Finally, after 5 hours total, he managed to get all the pieces, and myself and the Wizzie TPed over to Gfay where he got the last piece of the quest, and he gave the items over to us, and we gave him the Mithril BP. Cool Huh?<br>Myself and my two buddies have quite a nest egg tucked away from the 2 over years of playing (just to give you an idea of how much PP we have, each of us has another spare level 6 mule just to hold the cash, as our bank cannot hold that much)<br>and coz we three always work together, we rarely had to buy any uber equipment in the past (and also coz we are all wearing planes gear thanks to our connections with our previous guild)<br><br>So anyway... to summarise, this is not all about which gear is 'uber', this is a real fun way to hand out items for your twinks or to your very appreciative guildmates.<br><br>So go out there, stop leveling, and have fun!<br>Ta-Ta!<br><br>Xev<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
